TextSection.Contents: The term ''ectodermal dysplasia'' defines a heterogeneous group of heritable disorders of the skin and its appendages characterized by the defective development of two or more ectodermal derivatives including hair teeth nails sweat glands and their modified structures (i.e. ceruminous mammary and ciliary glands). The spectrum of clinical manifestations is wide and may include additional manifestations from other ectodermal mesodermal and endodermal structures.
